      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LUSH HOUR (4) recorded her 2nd career win last time at this track, scoring by a neck (30.24). Great chance again. MY LONG BLACK (3) made light work of the tricky draw with a fast early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing third (30.70) at this track over 525m. Won at his only start from this draw. Will give a great sight again. JUNEAU REST (2) flew the lids and led throughout to get off the mark with his maiden win, then finished a 7 length seventh last start at this track over 525m (30.71). Back to track where he won his maiden. Can turn it around this time. MAJOR IMPACT (8) did a good job to finish third last time out over 460m at Geelong (26.28) in a Mix 6/7, the second top-three finish on the trot.",
